The Irish housing sector has experienced increasing pressure from rising housing costs, limited housing supply and growing demand for emergency accommodation.
Public authorities require reliable, data-driven insights to understand regional homelessness patterns and support evidence-based decision making.

This project aims to transform multiple official Irish public datasets into a unified analytical solution that enables regional comparison,
identifies demographic trends and explores the relationship between homelessness, housing affordability and selected socio-economic indicators.

Business Questions
Which Irish regions experience the highest homelessness rates relative to their population?
Which demographic groups (gender and age) are most affected by homelessness?
Is there an observable association between homelessness, housing affordability, rental prices and unemployment?
Which regions may require greater attention when considering future housing support and policy planning?
